channel.description: Write an awesome description for your new site here. You can edit this line in _config.yml. It will appear in your document head meta (for Google search results) and in your feed.xml site description.

item.title: Barley
item.description: Barley is a web application for keeping track of your favorite beers. It's built on a node/express/mongo/backbone stack. This was a solo project thus I was responsible for the front and backend.

item.title: Get to Know Your Neighbors
item.description: The purpose of Get to Know Your Neighbors is to raise awareness around homeless issues. It's a web application built through ruby on rails. This was a group project in which my responsibilities included managing the git workflow and ad-hoc pairing on any front or backend issue.

item.title: GiFML
item.description: GiFML is a web app where users can create a gif mosaic encapsulating their personality and interests. It's written primarily in javascript and jQuery and was a solo project.

item.title: PoliConnect
item.description: Built using ruby on rails, PoliConnect is a platform to anonymously connect policy makers to policy experts in order to foster a frank dialogue that will ideally lead to better policy. This was built at D.C. Science Hack Day where our team took home the Policy Award. I contributed to the front and backend.

item.title: thisORthat
item.description: thisORthat is a frontend prototype for a social decision making app written in pure HTML/CSS. Test.
